## TypeTalks 2<br />Poznań, Sat–Sun 18–19 June 2011 ##

The two-days symposium took place at the **[University of Arts in Poznań (Poland)](Venue.html) on 18–19 June 2011**.

*The theme of our symposia is type and typography; this is not going to change any time soon. This year we aim to accentuate the social aspect of the symposium. After all, the word symposium refers to drinking parties or convivial discussions held in ancient Greece. The two days will include exhibitions, an evening full of short type presentations (aka TypeShorts), a party, and of course a day full of excellent lectures.*

The Poznań TypeTalks are organized in collaboration with the *University of Arts in Poznań* and *Foundation of the Academy of Fine Arts in Poznań*.

**Online registration has ended, but limited amount of places will be available on site at 42/66 € (student/normal).**
